               <scopecontent id="aspace_50bf5484ee68f4930b6dafd996ab70b5">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This area was colonized by the Belgians and known as the Belgian Congo prior to 1960 when it became The Republic of the Congo. The country was known as Zaire from 1971 to 1997 when the name was changed to the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) by President Laurent-Désiré Kabila after he overthrew President Joseph-Désiré Mobutu.</p>
               </scopecontent>
